The paper deals with formal languages and algorithms for retrieval from sequence databases, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The paper also discusses distance measures and similarity-based semantics, which are relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of normed vector distance measures and efficient algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper's focus on retrieval and querying suggests that it could belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of formalisms such as Automata, Temporal Logic, and Regular Expressions suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
